The Trump Administration has released a Coordinated Strategic Plan to Advance Desalination for Enhanced Water Security, in an effort to ensure the nation has continued access to secure and reliable water supplies. The plan aims to address challenges such as droughts, floods, and freshwater shortages that impact water infrastructure. It emphasizes the importance of water conservation efforts by both users and water utilities, as well as the development of new technologies to support access to clean water. The administration is committed to enhancing water security and solving future water availability and security challenges.